Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says Prasa will resume the Metrorail commuter services on July 1. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says Prasa will resume the Metrorail commuter services on 1 July. Mbalula briefed the media on advanced level 3 COVID-19 lockdown regulations and directives related to transport. Level 3 lockdown: Metrorail not ready to resume services Monday “Metrorail services are projected to resume on 1 July, subject to stringent safety measures being implemented. "The COVID-19 pandemic has worsened Prasa’s financial position, resulting in further cash constraints on an already strained financial situation,” said Mbalula. Long-distance rail services such as Shosholoza Meyl and Rovos Rail remains closed. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.